WEBVTT

00:02.085 --> 00:03.711
[melodic whistling]

00:03.795 --> 00:05.255
[smacking]

00:05.338 --> 00:06.423
[exhaling deeply]

00:06.506 --> 00:08.842
thump!
both: WHOA!

00:08.925 --> 00:10.719
- ♪ HERE WE GO 'CAUSE WE'RE
FANBOY AND CHUM CHUM ♪

00:10.802 --> 00:12.220
♪ A LITTLE CUCKOO,
FANBOY AND CHUM CHUM ♪

00:12.303 --> 00:13.596
♪ WE'RE AMAZING
TOTALLY CRAZY ♪

00:13.680 --> 00:14.597
♪ FANBOY AND CHUM CHUM ♪

00:14.681 --> 00:16.099
♪ COME ON, EVERYBODY, SING ♪

00:16.181 --> 00:17.767
♪ WE'RE GONNA SCREAM
AT THE TOP OF OUR LUNGS ♪

00:17.851 --> 00:19.436
♪ WE'RE GONNA FLY
AND HAVE SOME FUN ♪

00:19.519 --> 00:21.521
♪ WE DON'T CARE IF YOU STARE ♪

00:21.604 --> 00:22.480
♪ OR EVEN
LOOK AT OUR UNDERWEAR ♪

00:22.564 --> 00:24.941
both: ♪ BRAIN ♪

00:25.024 --> 00:26.985
♪ FREEZE ♪

00:27.068 --> 00:28.194
♪ OOH ♪

00:28.278 --> 00:29.612
♪ BRAIN FREEZE! ♪

00:29.696 --> 00:31.281
- ♪ BUH-BUH, BAH,
BAH, BAH, BAH, BAH, BAH ♪

00:31.364 --> 00:33.324
♪ BUH-BUH, BAH, BAH-BAH,
BUH, BAH-BAH, BAH ♪

00:33.408 --> 00:34.242
♪ BAH, BAH, BAH, BAH ♪

00:34.325 --> 00:36.828
♪ BUH-BUH, BAH-BAH,
BUH-BAH, BAH ♪

00:36.911 --> 00:38.788
♪ COME AND SCREAM
AT THE TOP OF YOUR LUNGS ♪

00:38.872 --> 00:40.165
♪ COME AND FLY
AND HAVE SOME FUN ♪

00:40.248 --> 00:41.166
♪ BUH-BUH, BAH ♪

00:41.249 --> 00:42.625
♪ BUH-BUH, BAH ♪

00:42.709 --> 00:44.127
♪ BUH-BUH, BAH, BAH,
FANBOY AND CHUM CHUM ♪

00:44.210 --> 00:45.336
both: OH!
- THAT'S NICE.

00:46.921 --> 00:50.008
[boisterous brass music]

00:50.091 --> 00:55.972
♪ ♪

00:57.974 --> 00:59.976
[alarm beeps]

01:00.059 --> 01:01.978
- ♪ TO... ♪

01:02.061 --> 01:03.229
- ♪ TO... ♪

01:03.313 --> 01:06.649
both: ♪ TO... ♪

01:06.733 --> 01:07.650
- ♪ TOGETHER ♪

01:07.734 --> 01:08.985
both: ♪ TOGETHER ♪

01:09.068 --> 01:10.069
♪ WE'RE FRIENDS,
FRIENDS, FRIENDS TOGETHER ♪

01:10.153 --> 01:12.280
- ♪ WE BOTH LIKE SWISS
AND CHEDDAR ♪

01:12.363 --> 01:13.364
- ♪ THOUGH WE DO
LIKE FETA BETTER ♪

01:13.448 --> 01:14.199
- ♪ TRUE ♪

01:14.282 --> 01:15.950
- ♪ TOGETHER ♪
- ♪ TOGETHER ♪

01:16.034 --> 01:17.327
- ♪ MY TENNIS SHOES
ARE LEATHER ♪

01:17.410 --> 01:18.119
- ♪ AND MINE
ARE PLASTIC PLEATHER ♪

01:18.203 --> 01:20.789
- ♪ YEAH, WE'RE STILL TOGETHER ♪

01:20.872 --> 01:22.332
- ♪ TOGETHER ♪
- ♪ TOGETHER ♪

01:22.415 --> 01:24.000
- ♪ WE BREAK
OUR BONES TOGETHER ♪

01:24.083 --> 01:25.710
- ♪ BUT FIXING THEM'S
A PLEASURE ♪

01:25.794 --> 01:29.923
- ♪ AND FUN BEYOND ALL MEASURE ♪

01:30.006 --> 01:32.675
- ♪ OUR FRIENDSHIP'S
WHAT WE TREASURE ♪

01:32.759 --> 01:35.094
- ♪ WHEN WE'RE AT OUR LEISURE ♪

01:35.178 --> 01:37.388
both: ♪ AS LONG
AS WE'RE TOGETHER ♪

01:37.472 --> 01:40.016
♪ I SWEAR THAT WE WILL NEVER ♪

01:40.099 --> 01:42.560
- BE QUIET!

01:42.644 --> 01:43.603
IT'S QUIET TIME.

01:43.686 --> 01:45.355
CAN'T YOU READ?

01:45.438 --> 01:47.732
- READING?

01:47.816 --> 01:50.109
I DON'T THINK
WE'VE COVERED THAT.

01:50.193 --> 01:52.695
- YEAH, WHAT GRADE
DO YOU THINK WE'RE IN?

01:52.779 --> 01:55.156
- WE'LL CALL THIS STRIKE ONE.

01:55.240 --> 01:55.949
NOW, TAKE YOUR SEATS.

01:56.032 --> 01:58.785
AND I DON'T WANT
TO HEAR A PEEP.

01:58.868 --> 02:00.745
I NEED ABSOLUTE QUIET
WHILE I WORK

02:00.829 --> 02:03.706
ON MY MODEL SWISS VILLAGE.

02:03.790 --> 02:04.958
OOH.

02:05.041 --> 02:06.918
WINTER'S COMING EARLY.

02:07.001 --> 02:08.211
[yodels]

02:08.294 --> 02:12.715
- FANBOY, WE DIDN'T GET
TO FINISH OUR SONG.

02:12.799 --> 02:14.968
- I KNOW.
WE ALWAYS FINISH OUR SONG.

02:15.051 --> 02:17.804
WAIT.
I HAVE AN IDEA.

02:17.887 --> 02:20.348
[giggles]

02:20.431 --> 02:22.308
both: ♪ I SWEAR THAT WE
WILL NEVER BE APART ♪

02:25.603 --> 02:27.814
♪ TOGETHER ♪

02:27.897 --> 02:29.899
- PHEW, THAT WAS CLOSE.

02:29.983 --> 02:30.984
- YEAH.

02:31.067 --> 02:32.485
HEY, FANBOY,
CAN I BORROW A PENCIL?

02:32.569 --> 02:33.570
- SURE, BUDDY.

02:33.653 --> 02:35.405
both: ♪ I SWEAR THAT WE
WILL NEVER BE APART ♪

02:35.488 --> 02:36.406
- UH-OH.

02:36.489 --> 02:37.657
[grunts]

02:38.992 --> 02:39.868
- THERE.

02:39.951 --> 02:42.287
THE LAST SNOWFLAKE IS IN PLACE,

02:42.370 --> 02:44.747
AND WITH NO TWO ALIKE.

02:44.831 --> 02:46.583
HUH? MEH.

02:46.666 --> 02:47.584
[singing and rumbling]

02:47.667 --> 02:49.669
HOLY SWISS CHEESE!

02:49.752 --> 02:52.088
[grunts]

02:52.171 --> 02:52.463
AH.

02:52.547 --> 02:56.426
OOH.

02:56.509 --> 02:56.759
- ♪ TOGETHER ♪

02:56.843 --> 02:59.304
- OH.

02:59.387 --> 03:00.513
AH.

03:00.597 --> 03:06.102
OH, MY BEAUTIFUL LITTLE TOWN
OF MUFFLINFLUSEN.

03:06.185 --> 03:07.979
[groans]

03:08.062 --> 03:12.233
I AM SO ANGRY,
I CAN SEE STRAIGHT.

03:12.317 --> 03:14.110
THAT'S STRIKE TWO.

03:14.193 --> 03:16.487
TIME FOR YOUR PUNISHMENT.

03:16.571 --> 03:18.656
- PUNISHMENT?
BUT DON'T WE GET THREE STRIKES?

03:18.740 --> 03:21.451
- OOH, OOH, BACK SASS.

03:21.534 --> 03:23.494
ISN'T THAT STRIKE THREE?

03:23.578 --> 03:24.787
- THE BUTT-KISSER'S RIGHT.

03:24.871 --> 03:26.247
- THANK YOU.

03:26.331 --> 03:29.959
- YOU LEAVE ME NO CHOICE BUT...

03:30.043 --> 03:33.212
TO SEPARATE YOUR DESKS!

03:33.296 --> 03:34.297
- [gasps]

03:34.380 --> 03:36.007
- SEPARATE OUR DESKS?

03:36.090 --> 03:38.426
- PLEASE, MR. MUFFLIN,
ANYTHING BUT THAT.

03:38.509 --> 03:39.802
WE'RE SORRY.

03:39.886 --> 03:44.140
- SORRY WON'T SAVE THOSE POOR
TRAPPED MUFFLINFLUSIANS.

03:44.223 --> 03:44.682
YOU'RE COMING UP FRONT.

03:44.766 --> 03:46.768
[metal grating]

03:46.851 --> 03:48.227
- CHUM CHUM!

03:48.311 --> 03:49.145
thwap!

03:49.228 --> 03:49.562
- WHAT THE?

03:49.646 --> 03:50.647
both: MMM.

03:50.730 --> 03:52.941
- [grumbling]

03:53.024 --> 03:53.983
- [grunting]

03:54.067 --> 03:54.984
- YAH!

03:55.068 --> 03:56.319
- [grunts]

03:56.402 --> 03:57.320
thwap!

03:57.403 --> 03:58.738
- HEH?
- HUH?

03:58.821 --> 04:01.157
[chuckles] MUST BE THE MAGNETIC
POWER OF OUR FRIENDSHIP.

04:01.240 --> 04:02.742
- [groaning]

04:02.825 --> 04:03.993
OOH!

04:04.077 --> 04:06.579
[grunts]

04:06.663 --> 04:07.580
HUH?

04:07.664 --> 04:08.623
thwap!

04:08.706 --> 04:10.333
[both laugh]

04:10.416 --> 04:13.378
- [groans loudly]

04:13.461 --> 04:15.463
[grunting and groaning]

04:18.257 --> 04:19.425
- [giggles]

04:22.011 --> 04:22.971
- WHOA.

04:23.054 --> 04:24.347
- [groans]

04:24.430 --> 04:25.682
- FANBOY!

04:25.765 --> 04:28.184
- CHUM CHUM!

04:28.267 --> 04:28.977
NO, MR. MUFFLIN. PLEASE.

04:29.060 --> 04:30.895
YOU CAN'T SEPARATE US.

04:30.979 --> 04:31.896
WE NEED TO BE TOGETHER.

04:31.980 --> 04:33.856
IT'S OUR ANCIENT
CHINESE DESTINY.

04:33.940 --> 04:34.983
PLE-HE-HE-HEASE.

04:35.066 --> 04:36.025
HE CAN'T LIVE WITHOUT ME.

04:36.109 --> 04:37.026
WE'LL SHARE A KIDNEY.

04:37.110 --> 04:38.069
NO!

04:38.152 --> 04:39.320
IT'LL--IT'LL--

04:39.404 --> 04:41.322
IT'LL RIP A HOLE
IN THE SPACE-TIME CONTINUUM.

04:41.406 --> 04:44.701
THE FATE OF THE UNIVERSE
IS AT STAKE!

04:44.784 --> 04:47.704
- QUIT YOUR NONSENSICAL
TAMSHANNERY.

04:47.787 --> 04:49.205
- HA-HA.
YOU GOT IN TROUBLE.

04:49.288 --> 04:50.206
OH.

04:50.289 --> 04:51.874
- THERE.

04:51.958 --> 04:54.502
I'M GONNA BE WATCHING YOU,

04:54.585 --> 04:57.505
BOTH OF YOU.

04:59.465 --> 05:01.259
- CHUM CHUM.

05:04.804 --> 05:07.807
[crying] CHUM CHUM.

05:09.976 --> 05:14.230
"MY DEAREST CHUM CHUM,

05:14.313 --> 05:17.066
"THE 2 1/2 MINUTES
WE HAVE BEEN SEPARATED PAIN ME

05:17.150 --> 05:19.902
LIKE THE TIME I TRIED TO GRAB
THAT HOT DOG WITH MY TONGUE."

05:19.986 --> 05:23.906
[screams]

05:23.990 --> 05:26.242
[groans]

05:26.325 --> 05:28.453
"SOMETIMES I THINK I HEAR
YOUR GENTLE VOICE

05:28.536 --> 05:29.579
"FALL ABOUT MY EAR.

05:29.662 --> 05:31.164
"BUT THEN I REALIZE
IT'S JUST THE SQUISH-SQUISH

05:31.247 --> 05:33.666
OF DUKE GIVING ME A WET WILLY."

05:33.750 --> 05:34.709
[grunts]

05:34.792 --> 05:35.585
DUKE.

05:35.668 --> 05:37.503
"I MUST BRING THIS LETTER
TO A CLOSE,

05:37.587 --> 05:41.466
"AS IT APPEARS SPITBALL WINTER
HAS COME EARLY THIS YEAR.

05:41.549 --> 05:44.093
"I REMAIN, AS ALWAYS,
YOUR DEVOTED BEST BUDDY,

05:44.177 --> 05:49.724
LANCE CORPORAL TOBIAS
CRANAPPLE FANBOY III, DDS."

05:52.143 --> 05:53.269
- "DEAR FANBOY,

05:53.352 --> 05:54.270
"HI.

05:54.353 --> 05:56.355
"THINGS STINK AROUND HERE
WITHOUT YOU.

05:56.439 --> 05:58.733
CHRIS CHUGGY KEEPS TRYING
TO GET ME TO SMELL HIS FINGER."

05:58.816 --> 05:59.609
- WAH-WAH.

05:59.692 --> 06:00.943
- "IF YOU MISS ME,
CHECK THIS BOX.

06:01.027 --> 06:03.738
"OKAY, SMELL YOU LATER.

06:03.821 --> 06:05.615
"NOT YOU, CHRIS. STOP IT.

06:05.698 --> 06:07.700
YOUR BFF FOREVER, CHUM CHUM."

06:07.784 --> 06:09.577
[sniffs]

06:09.660 --> 06:11.996
- MM.

06:12.080 --> 06:15.792
YES, CHUM CHUM,
I WILL CHECK THIS BOX.

06:17.752 --> 06:19.921
splat!

06:22.673 --> 06:23.633
KYLE.

06:23.716 --> 06:24.967
smack!

06:25.051 --> 06:26.469
YOU MUST CARRY
THIS LETTER TO CHUM CHUM.

06:26.552 --> 06:26.969
AND I IMPLORE YOU,
MAKE HASTE.

06:27.053 --> 06:28.763
DO NOT TARRY.

06:28.846 --> 06:30.598
- OH, FOR HEAVEN'S SAKE.

06:30.681 --> 06:32.809
HERE.

06:32.892 --> 06:35.978
[chomps]

06:36.062 --> 06:37.021
- DID HE GET IT?

06:37.105 --> 06:37.980
GOOD.

06:38.064 --> 06:39.816
NOW TELL HIM I WILL NOT REST

06:39.899 --> 06:42.110
UNTIL WE ARE REUNITED.

06:42.193 --> 06:43.903
- ♪ HMM-HMM-HMM
HMM-HMM-HMM ♪

06:43.986 --> 06:44.529
♪ HMM-HMM-HMM ♪

06:51.452 --> 06:53.412
[mechanical whirring]

06:54.872 --> 06:56.457
[rumbling]

06:56.541 --> 06:58.292
[whooshing]

07:00.461 --> 07:02.880
[descending whistle sound]

07:05.258 --> 07:05.716
- AHHH!

07:05.800 --> 07:08.010
- OH.

07:08.094 --> 07:09.720
- [grunting]

07:09.804 --> 07:11.639
AH!

07:13.099 --> 07:15.059
[gong crashes]

07:15.143 --> 07:16.561
- STRIKE FOUR?

07:18.312 --> 07:19.522
- MR. MUFFLIN?

07:19.605 --> 07:20.898
- WHAT IS IT?

07:20.982 --> 07:23.067
- UM, I DROPPED MY PENCIL.

07:23.151 --> 07:24.694
AND I CAN'T REACH IT.

07:24.777 --> 07:25.862
COULD YOU GET IT FOR ME?

07:25.945 --> 07:28.030
- OH.

07:28.114 --> 07:29.657
WHERE IS IT?

07:29.740 --> 07:31.367
- IT ROLLED UNDER THE...

07:31.450 --> 07:33.828
SCHOOL.

07:33.911 --> 07:36.998
- UGH. AGAIN?

07:38.958 --> 07:41.878
[thumping]

07:41.961 --> 07:43.963
[cranking]

07:45.339 --> 07:46.465
[metal straining]

07:49.635 --> 07:50.678
[lever cranks]

07:52.763 --> 07:55.808
- AH.

07:55.892 --> 07:56.809
[needle scratches]

07:56.893 --> 07:58.895
- GOING SOMEWHERE?

07:58.978 --> 08:01.063
- UH-UH.

08:03.232 --> 08:03.941
[car puttering]

08:04.025 --> 08:08.154
- [humming]

08:12.658 --> 08:15.203
[electricity hisses]

08:16.704 --> 08:18.915
[mechanical whirring]

08:20.958 --> 08:24.086
- AH.

08:25.296 --> 08:26.297
both: AH!

08:26.380 --> 08:28.925
- ONE MORE HOLE.

08:29.008 --> 08:29.675
THAT'S IT.

08:29.759 --> 08:33.095
NOW, THAT'S WHAT I CALL SWISS--

08:33.179 --> 08:34.847
CHEESE AND MACARONI!

08:34.931 --> 08:35.932
AH!

08:36.015 --> 08:37.099
[all sigh]

08:37.183 --> 08:39.227
- OOH, THIS IS FUN.

08:39.309 --> 08:40.519
both: WHOA!

08:40.602 --> 08:41.645
- NO!

08:45.024 --> 08:46.025
- OOPSIE. HEH.

08:46.108 --> 08:47.526
AUF WIEDERSEHEN.

08:47.610 --> 08:48.110
- OOH-AH.

08:48.194 --> 08:50.196
OH, SWEET MUFFLINFLUSEN.

08:50.279 --> 08:51.948
[crying] OH. OOH.

08:52.031 --> 08:53.783
YOU TWO!

08:53.866 --> 08:57.578
YOU DESTROYED
MUFFLINFLUSEN!

08:57.662 --> 08:58.496
THAT'S IT.

08:58.579 --> 09:00.665
I AM SEPARATING YOU TWO

09:00.748 --> 09:02.583
PERMANENTLY.

09:02.667 --> 09:04.168
both: WHAT?

09:04.252 --> 09:06.796
- I'M GONNA SEE TO IT
YOU'RE IN SEPARATE CLASSROOMS,

09:06.879 --> 09:09.507
MAYBE EVEN SEPARATE SCHOOLS.

09:09.590 --> 09:12.218
- NO!

09:12.301 --> 09:13.135
- NO, MR. MUFFLIN. PLEASE.

09:13.219 --> 09:15.137
CHINESE DESTINY.
KIDNEY.

09:15.221 --> 09:17.473
SPACE-TIME CONTINUUM!

09:17.557 --> 09:19.850
- YEAH, YEAH,
FATE OF THE UNIVERSE.

09:19.934 --> 09:23.813
I'VE HEARD IT ALL BE--
FOR THE LOVE OF LEDERHOSEN!

09:23.896 --> 09:24.814
- WAH-WAH.

09:24.897 --> 09:27.316
- YAH!

09:27.400 --> 09:27.984
- AH. HO-HO.

09:28.067 --> 09:31.529
- MAN-ARCTICA.

09:31.612 --> 09:33.281
- WHERE AM I?

09:33.364 --> 09:35.574
I WAS JUST FIGHTING
GLAXNOR THE SPACE SQUID

09:35.658 --> 09:37.326
IN THE ZETA-JONES QUADRANT.

09:37.410 --> 09:38.160
IT'S AS IF A HOLE'S
BEEN RIPPED

09:38.244 --> 09:41.289
IN THE SPACE-TIME CONTINUUM.

09:41.372 --> 09:43.416
- SPACE? TIME?

09:43.499 --> 09:43.916
OH, DEAR.

09:44.000 --> 09:46.669
- [gasps]

09:46.752 --> 09:48.546
ORANGE KID THERE.

09:48.629 --> 09:50.673
PURPLE KID HERE.

09:50.756 --> 09:53.384
GREAT CAESAR'S ICE FLOE.

09:53.467 --> 09:56.012
WHAT IDIOT SEPARATED
THESE BOYS' DESKS?

09:56.095 --> 09:58.347
- UH. UH.

09:58.431 --> 10:01.684
WELL, UH--WELL, THE PURPLE ONE
SMASHED MY GLOCKENSPIEL.

10:01.767 --> 10:02.643
smack!

10:02.727 --> 10:04.186
- YOU FOOL!

10:04.270 --> 10:06.689
DON'T YOU KNOW THAT
BY SEPARATING THEIR DESKS,

10:06.772 --> 10:09.984
YOU'VE PUT THE FATE
OF THE ENTIRE UNIVERSE AT STAKE?

10:10.067 --> 10:11.944
- I TRIED TO TELL HIM!

10:12.028 --> 10:14.196
- UM, LITTLE HELP HERE?

10:14.280 --> 10:15.281
I SEEM TO BE CAUGHT
IN THE TENTACLES

10:15.364 --> 10:18.034
OF AN INTERGALACTIC BEAST.

10:18.117 --> 10:18.993
- GLAXNOR.

10:19.076 --> 10:21.245
FEAR NOT, FOPPY CITIZEN
OF THE GALAXY.

10:21.329 --> 10:23.289
THERE'S NOT MUCH TIME, BOYS.

10:23.372 --> 10:26.625
YOU KNOW WHAT MUST BE DONE.

10:26.709 --> 10:28.210
- MM-HMM.

10:28.294 --> 10:29.086
- [grunts]

10:29.170 --> 10:32.381
- [grunting]

10:41.015 --> 10:42.808
- AH!

10:46.354 --> 10:49.649
[zapping]

10:49.732 --> 10:52.068
[sonic whooshing]

10:54.111 --> 10:54.779
[groaning]

10:56.947 --> 10:59.116
- OH, THANK YOU,
MAN-ARTICA.

10:59.200 --> 11:01.410
- THAT'S MAN-ARCTICA,

11:01.494 --> 11:03.287
WITH A HARD "C" IN THE MIDDLE.

11:03.371 --> 11:04.789
IT'S TRICKY.

11:04.872 --> 11:08.292
MAN-ARCTICA OUT.

11:08.376 --> 11:09.126
- HIYA, CHUM CHUM.

11:09.210 --> 11:11.379
YOU MISS ME?

11:11.462 --> 11:12.963
- DOES GLAXNOR POOP
AN ASTEROID BELT?

11:13.047 --> 11:15.299
- AH.

11:15.383 --> 11:18.969
NOW, THAT'S HOW YOU RESTORE
BALANCE TO THE UNIVERSE.

11:19.053 --> 11:21.764
- I'LL NEVER MOVE
THIS DESK AGAIN.

11:21.847 --> 11:23.140
- OKAY.

11:23.224 --> 11:24.141
[squeaking fart]

11:24.225 --> 11:25.267
[giggles]

11:25.351 --> 11:26.894
- EW.
[giggles]

11:26.977 --> 11:29.563
MR. MUFFLIN,
CAN I MOVE SEATS?

11:29.647 --> 11:30.231
MR. MUFFLIN?

11:30.314 --> 11:32.108
[wind whipping]

11:32.191 --> 11:33.734
WHERE'D HE GO?

11:33.818 --> 11:37.655
- [yodeling quietly]

11:44.203 --> 11:47.039
[boisterous orchestral music]

11:47.123 --> 11:52.002
♪ ♪

11:52.711 --> 11:56.048
[Fanboy and Chum Chum humming]

12:01.971 --> 12:03.722
- LOOK WHAT I DREW.

12:03.806 --> 12:06.308
- DUDE, COOL SQUID ON A BIKE.

12:08.018 --> 12:10.813
HEY, CHECK OUT MY PICTURE.

12:10.896 --> 12:12.523
- WOW. THAT'S A GREAT...

12:12.606 --> 12:13.983
EGGPLANT?

12:14.066 --> 12:15.943
- IT'S ME, YOU GOOF.

12:16.026 --> 12:17.153
- [giggles]

12:17.236 --> 12:19.488
[laughter]

12:19.572 --> 12:20.865
[groans]

12:20.948 --> 12:22.074
- WAH-HA-HA-HA!

12:22.158 --> 12:24.160
HEY!

12:24.243 --> 12:26.078
[giggling quietly]

12:26.162 --> 12:27.830
- FANBOY?

12:27.913 --> 12:29.290
- [giggling quietly]

12:29.373 --> 12:32.376
[laughs hysterically]

12:32.460 --> 12:34.795
OH, YOU'RE GONNA GET IT NOW.

12:34.879 --> 12:35.171
AH-HA!

12:35.254 --> 12:37.006
- OH, NO.

12:37.089 --> 12:38.340
OH, NO!

12:38.424 --> 12:41.969
[laughter]

12:43.596 --> 12:46.390
[slow-motion groaning]

12:48.767 --> 12:49.727
[both gasp]

12:49.810 --> 12:52.855
- OOH, I SURE HOPE
THAT DOESN'T...

12:52.938 --> 12:53.856
crash!

12:53.939 --> 12:54.899
HIT ANYTHING.

12:54.982 --> 12:57.359
[cars crashing]
[people screaming]

12:57.443 --> 12:58.611
- NOBODY'S HURT.

12:58.694 --> 13:00.321
- AND THEY ALL LOOK
LIKE GOOD SWIMMERS.

13:00.404 --> 13:02.698
SO IT'S A HAPPY ENDING
AFTER ALL.

13:02.781 --> 13:05.075
HEY, LOOK.

13:05.159 --> 13:05.701
- OOH.

13:05.784 --> 13:06.827
IT'S ONE OF THOSE BUBBLES

13:06.911 --> 13:10.915
THAT ALWAYS HAS
A BEAUTIFUL FAIRY IN IT.

13:10.998 --> 13:12.791
[giggles]

13:14.168 --> 13:16.253
honk!

13:16.337 --> 13:19.298
WELL, I BET SHE HAS
A GREAT PERSONALITY.

13:19.381 --> 13:21.133
- YEAH, YEAH, YEAH,
SAVE IT.

13:21.217 --> 13:21.967
THE FAIRY HAD A DATE TONIGHT,

13:22.051 --> 13:24.178
AND I NEED THE OVERTIME,
ALL RIGHT?

13:24.261 --> 13:26.555
- SO WHAT'S UP?

13:26.639 --> 13:27.890
- UH, LET'S SEE.

13:27.973 --> 13:31.018
IT SAYS HERE I'M SUPPOSED
TO PUNISH FANBOY

13:31.101 --> 13:31.936
'CAUSE YOU'VE BEEN NAUGHTY.

13:32.019 --> 13:34.647
- ME?
NO, THERE MUST BE SOME MISTAKE.

13:34.730 --> 13:37.733
I BET YOU'RE LOOKING
FOR BANFOY.

13:37.816 --> 13:40.236
- YEAH, FANBOY'S NEVER NAUGHTY.

13:40.319 --> 13:44.615
- MM-HMM.

13:44.698 --> 13:46.158
NEVER NAUGHTY, HUH?

13:46.242 --> 13:48.577
[laughter]

13:48.661 --> 13:50.079
- [blows sharply] OH, YEAH.

13:50.162 --> 13:51.580
HIGH FIVE. HIGH FIVE.
HIGH FIVE.

13:51.664 --> 13:52.873
LOW FIVE?

13:52.957 --> 13:53.916
- [growling]

13:55.751 --> 13:58.045
- MM-HMM.

13:58.128 --> 13:59.463
MM-HMM.

13:59.547 --> 14:00.631
- [humming]

14:00.714 --> 14:02.675
- [grumbles]

14:03.717 --> 14:04.593
- TEE-HEE-HEE-HEE.

14:04.677 --> 14:05.803
[giggles]

14:05.886 --> 14:06.804
thoonk!

14:06.887 --> 14:08.222
- AH!

14:09.014 --> 14:11.767
- WOW.
I GOT A LOT DONE TODAY.

14:11.850 --> 14:14.687
- YOU ARE
A NAUGHTY LITTLE KNOT HEAD.

14:14.770 --> 14:16.939
SO YOU MIGHT AS WELL
BE MADE OF WOOD.

14:17.022 --> 14:18.023
[electrical zapping]

14:18.107 --> 14:19.358
- UH-OH.

14:19.441 --> 14:20.901
- BADDA-BING, BADDA-BOOM.

14:20.985 --> 14:22.528
- [gasps]

14:26.865 --> 14:28.075
- [gasps]

14:28.158 --> 14:30.411
FANBOY, ARE YOU OKAY?

14:30.494 --> 14:33.455
SPEAK TO ME.

14:33.539 --> 14:36.792
[gasps]

14:36.875 --> 14:39.211
- MY--MY ARMS ARE WOOD.

14:41.755 --> 14:43.132
MY LEGS ARE WOOD.

14:43.215 --> 14:44.800
I'M NOT A BOY ANYMORE.

14:44.883 --> 14:47.720
I'M A WOODEN TOY.

14:47.803 --> 14:49.638
THIS IS...

14:49.722 --> 14:51.765
AWESOME!

14:51.849 --> 14:53.434
- AWESOME, YOU SAY?

14:53.517 --> 14:55.936
BUT WHY IS BEING A TOY AWESOME?

14:56.020 --> 14:58.355
- WELL, I'LL TELL YOU.

14:58.439 --> 15:00.816
♪ I... ♪

15:00.899 --> 15:04.945
- I NEED LESS SINGING,
MORE MISERY.

15:05.029 --> 15:07.823
'CAUSE IF I CAN'T CHECK THE BOX
THAT SAYS YOU EMITTED--

15:07.906 --> 15:10.117
WHAT IS THIS--
"SHRIEKS OF AGONY

15:10.200 --> 15:11.660
AND/OR CRYING AND WAILING,"

15:11.744 --> 15:14.204
I AIN'T GONNA MEET MY QUOTA.

15:14.288 --> 15:16.248
- BUT WHY SHOULD I BE UPSET?

15:16.332 --> 15:17.333
I'VE GOT PAINTED-ON UNDERWEAR,

15:17.416 --> 15:19.835
A SPRING-LOADED JAW.

15:19.918 --> 15:24.340
- AND HE'S DELICIOUS
ON PANCAKES.

15:24.423 --> 15:25.674
- LOOK, IF YOU'RE NOT
GONNA BE MISERABLE,

15:25.758 --> 15:28.385
I GOT TO TURN YOU BACK
INTO A BOY.

15:28.469 --> 15:29.345
IT'S COMPANY POLICY.

15:29.428 --> 15:31.347
- WAIT, NO.

15:31.430 --> 15:32.348
DON'T YOU UNDERSTAND?

15:32.431 --> 15:33.349
I HAVE TO BE A TOY.

15:33.432 --> 15:34.391
THERE'S GOT TO BE A WAY.

15:34.475 --> 15:37.102
THIS IS MY...

15:37.186 --> 15:40.606
DESTINY!

15:40.689 --> 15:44.026
- OH, YOU'RE BREAKING
MY HEART HERE.

15:44.109 --> 15:45.778
FINE, I'LL LET YOU STAY A TOY.

15:45.861 --> 15:47.655
both: YAY!

15:47.738 --> 15:49.823
- ALL RIGHT, I'M GONNA NEED YOU
TO SIGN HERE, HERE,

15:49.907 --> 15:51.617
AND INITIAL HERE.

15:51.700 --> 15:53.452
- HMM, WHERE DID I PUT
THAT PENCIL?

15:53.535 --> 15:54.870
OH, YEAH.

15:54.953 --> 15:56.789
[whirring]
EEE.

15:56.872 --> 15:57.873
[blows sharply]

15:57.956 --> 15:59.458
UH-HUH-HEH-HEH-HEH.

15:59.541 --> 16:02.252
AND "X" OVER HERE.

16:02.336 --> 16:04.213
- NOW, FOR THIS TO WORK,

16:04.296 --> 16:07.383
YOU GOT TO DO ONE GOOD DEED
BY 5:00 TODAY.

16:07.466 --> 16:08.509
CAN YOU DO THAT, CHIEF?

16:08.592 --> 16:10.761
- [laughing] CAN I--
CAN I DO THAT?

16:10.844 --> 16:12.137
OF COURSE I CAN.

16:12.221 --> 16:14.098
I AM GOOD ALL THE TIME.

16:14.181 --> 16:15.849
HUH?

16:15.933 --> 16:19.061
UH, OKAY.
I DON'T KNOW WHAT THAT IS.

16:19.144 --> 16:22.648
ALL THAT MATTERS IS,
I AM GONNA BE SO GOOD.

16:22.731 --> 16:23.899
AH.

16:23.982 --> 16:25.192
SO GENEROUS?

16:25.275 --> 16:26.735
CIVILIZED?
CONSIDERATE?

16:26.819 --> 16:27.444
HELPFUL?

16:27.528 --> 16:30.155
NOT QUITE AS TERRIBLE?

16:30.239 --> 16:32.408
- AH!
crash!

16:32.491 --> 16:34.076
[cat shrieks]

16:34.159 --> 16:35.160
[school bell rings]

16:35.244 --> 16:36.453
COME ON, CHUM CHUM.

16:36.537 --> 16:37.579
WE GOT TO FIND A GOOD DEED,

16:37.663 --> 16:40.290
SO KEEP YOUR EYES PEELED.

16:40.374 --> 16:42.751
MINE TOO.

16:42.835 --> 16:44.503
THAT'S BETTER.

16:44.586 --> 16:46.380
- HEY, LOOK.
- HMM?

16:47.840 --> 16:49.633
HELPING A GIRL WITH HER BOOKS.

16:49.717 --> 16:52.219
HO-HO, THAT'S PERFECT.

16:52.302 --> 16:54.263
- AY!

16:54.346 --> 16:55.764
- EXCUSE ME, MADAM.

16:55.848 --> 16:58.183
MAY I HELP YOU WITH YOUR BOOKS?

16:58.267 --> 16:59.852
- AY, FANBOY.

16:59.935 --> 17:03.105
YOU ARE MY KNIGHT
IN EH-SHINING...

17:03.188 --> 17:06.775
WEIRD TALL THING WITH WHEELS.

17:06.858 --> 17:10.362
- ALLOW ME, MADAM.

17:10.445 --> 17:12.573
- WHY ARE YOU DROPPING THEM?

17:12.656 --> 17:13.449
- EH, OOPS. SORRY.

17:13.531 --> 17:14.450
[groans]

17:14.532 --> 17:15.617
GOT IT. NOPE.

17:15.701 --> 17:18.412
[strains] GOT IT. NOPE.

17:18.494 --> 17:18.912
GOT--NOPE.

17:18.996 --> 17:19.997
OKAY, ONE SECOND.

17:20.079 --> 17:22.374
[grunts] CAN'T SEEM
TO GRAB AHOLD OF THE BOOKS.

17:22.458 --> 17:25.461
[groans]

17:25.544 --> 17:27.296
- I GIVE UP.

17:27.378 --> 17:28.130
I DO IT.

17:28.213 --> 17:30.257
- NO, NO, NO.
IT'S UNDER CONTROL.

17:30.340 --> 17:30.716
[groans]

17:30.799 --> 17:32.593
GOT IT. NOPE.

17:32.676 --> 17:35.095
[both groaning]

17:35.179 --> 17:36.805
- EH-STOP HELPING.

17:36.889 --> 17:37.264
- BUT MY GOOD DEED.

17:37.347 --> 17:39.349
- AY!

17:39.433 --> 17:40.517
crash!
[cat shrieks]

17:43.771 --> 17:44.730
[watch ticking]

17:44.813 --> 17:45.647
- EH, WE'RE RUNNING OUT
OF TIME.

17:45.731 --> 17:50.277
[baby cooing]

17:50.360 --> 17:51.278
HA. PAY DIRT.

17:53.280 --> 17:54.364
PARDON ME, MISS.

17:54.448 --> 17:55.407
BUT YOUR BABY DROPPED
HIS RATTLE.

17:55.491 --> 17:56.784
ALLOW ME.

17:56.867 --> 17:59.828
- WELL, AREN'T YOU
A SWEET PUPPET.

17:59.912 --> 18:02.498
- AW, WHAT A CUTIE.

18:02.581 --> 18:04.458
I GOT TO KISS THAT LITTLE FACE.

18:04.541 --> 18:05.417
chomp!

18:05.501 --> 18:06.460
- AH!

18:06.543 --> 18:07.503
[woman screams]

18:07.586 --> 18:09.838
- FANBOY, LET GO.

18:09.922 --> 18:12.216
- UH, HELLO,
SPRING-LOADED JAW.

18:12.299 --> 18:13.425
[rattle conking]

18:13.509 --> 18:16.637
- MAYBE GOOD DEEDS
FOR ANIMALS ARE EASIER.

18:16.720 --> 18:18.806
- [groaning]

18:20.766 --> 18:23.560
crash!
[car alarm blaring]

18:23.644 --> 18:24.520
[tires squeal]

18:24.603 --> 18:25.521
- HIT IT.

18:25.604 --> 18:28.357
[tires squealing]

18:28.440 --> 18:31.193
snap!

18:31.276 --> 18:32.611
- NO WONDER
WE NEVER DO GOOD DEEDS.

18:32.694 --> 18:35.114
IT'S HARD.

18:35.197 --> 18:37.449
- WELL, IN OUR DEFENSE,
WE'RE USUALLY PRETTY BUSY.

18:37.533 --> 18:39.743
LOOK.

18:39.827 --> 18:40.702
AN OLD LADY'S
ABOUT TO CROSS THE STREET.

18:40.786 --> 18:44.414
- OH, THAT IS A CLASSIC.

18:44.498 --> 18:45.833
WE CAN'T LOSE.

18:45.916 --> 18:46.875
OZ'S MOM,

18:46.959 --> 18:50.546
MAY I HELP YOU CROSS
THE STREET?

18:50.629 --> 18:53.757
- I'M JUST WALKING
TO MY HIP-HOP KARATE CLASS,

18:53.841 --> 18:56.635
BUT SURE, WHY NOT?

18:56.718 --> 18:59.429
- GET YOUR STUMPS OFF HER.

18:59.513 --> 19:01.557
- BOOG, YOU'RE MADE OF WOOD?

19:01.640 --> 19:02.850
THAT'S IMPOSSIBLE.

19:02.933 --> 19:04.434
I'M THE WOODEN TOY AROUND HERE.

19:04.518 --> 19:05.602
IT'S MY DESTINY.

19:05.686 --> 19:08.897
- UH, WRONG AGAIN,
BALSA BREATH.

19:08.981 --> 19:11.191
YO, NICE GESTURING.

19:11.275 --> 19:12.317
[chuckles]

19:12.401 --> 19:13.694
- EH, IF YOU'RE FORCED
TO DO SOMETHING,

19:13.777 --> 19:15.070
I SAY DO IT WELL.

19:15.153 --> 19:17.406
- HEY, SHOULDN'T YOU
HAVE GOTTEN LOST ALREADY?

19:17.489 --> 19:18.657
OUT OF MY WAY.

19:18.740 --> 19:20.492
I GOT TO GET ALL HELPY
WITH GRANDMA HERE

19:20.576 --> 19:22.452
SO I CAN STAY WOOD
AND EVERYTHING.

19:22.536 --> 19:23.370
- STAY WOOD, YOU SAY?

19:23.453 --> 19:26.248
BUT WHY WOULD BOOG
WANT TO STAY WOOD?

19:26.331 --> 19:30.127
- WELL, I'LL TELL YOU.

19:30.210 --> 19:31.086
- OW.

19:31.169 --> 19:32.337
- [laughing] THAT WAS GOOD.

19:32.421 --> 19:33.046
YOU HEAR THAT BEAUTIFUL SOUND?

19:33.130 --> 19:35.924
I GOT THE MAHOGANY OF BOPS,

19:36.008 --> 19:38.010
AND I AIN'T GIVING IT UP.

19:38.093 --> 19:38.594
both: AH!

19:38.677 --> 19:40.596
[cat shrieks]

19:40.679 --> 19:41.972
- COME ON, GRANDMA.

19:42.055 --> 19:42.598
I WOULDN'T WANT YOU
TO RUST UP ON ME NOW.

19:42.681 --> 19:45.601
[humming]

19:45.684 --> 19:47.519
HEY.

19:47.603 --> 19:49.521
[rumbling]

19:49.605 --> 19:50.105
- THAT SOUNDS LIKE A...

19:50.188 --> 19:52.774
both: BOWLING BALL!

19:52.858 --> 19:54.776
- STEE-RIKE!

19:54.860 --> 19:56.236
[laughs]

19:58.071 --> 19:59.114
GET LOST.

19:59.197 --> 20:00.032
- SHE'S MINE.

20:00.115 --> 20:01.074
- NO, SHE'S MINE.

20:01.158 --> 20:02.451
- NO, SHE'S MINE.

20:02.534 --> 20:03.493
- NO, SHE'S MINE.

20:03.577 --> 20:05.454
[both grunt]

20:05.537 --> 20:07.414
[both grunting]

20:11.627 --> 20:13.462
- HEY, ARE WE
ROLLING DOWNHILL?

20:13.545 --> 20:16.548
all: WHOA!

20:16.632 --> 20:19.176
- AH!

20:19.259 --> 20:20.302
REMEMBER HIP-HOP TRAINING.

20:21.637 --> 20:24.723
[all shouting]

20:29.561 --> 20:34.066
SENSEI MIX MASTER "G"
IS GONNA BE SO PROUD OF ME.

20:34.149 --> 20:36.485
- OH, WHAT A BEAUTIFUL DAY.

20:36.568 --> 20:38.070
CAN I HAVE A HUG?

20:38.153 --> 20:40.489
- YOU SURE CAN.

20:40.572 --> 20:42.991
- OH-HO-HO-HO.

20:43.075 --> 20:44.868
[kid snoring]

20:44.952 --> 20:46.370
[both giggling]

20:46.453 --> 20:47.621
crash!

20:47.704 --> 20:49.665
[watch beeping]

20:52.918 --> 20:53.669
- TELL ME
THAT WASN'T FIVE BEEPS.

20:53.752 --> 20:55.879
- IT WAS.

20:55.963 --> 20:56.838
TIME'S UP.

20:56.922 --> 20:59.132
- YOU COST ME MY GOOD DEED.

20:59.216 --> 20:59.591
both: HUH?

20:59.675 --> 21:01.843
all: HUH?

21:01.927 --> 21:03.553
- WELL, THANKS
FOR MAKING ME FILL OUT

21:03.637 --> 21:05.263
ALL THOSE FORMS FOR NOTHING.

21:05.347 --> 21:07.683
NOW I GOT TO TURN YOU BACK
INTO BOYS.

21:07.766 --> 21:08.892
- WAIT.
IT'S NOT MY FAULT.

21:08.976 --> 21:09.851
HE RUINED MY GOOD DEED.

21:09.935 --> 21:13.313
- NO, HE RUINED MY GOOD DEED.

21:13.397 --> 21:15.774
AND I'M GONNA BOP HIM GOOD
BEFORE I GO FULL BOY AGAIN.

21:15.857 --> 21:17.693
- OW.
- BOP!

21:17.776 --> 21:19.027
- HAIL-DI-BOP-DI-BOP!

21:19.111 --> 21:21.154
[grunts]

21:21.238 --> 21:22.322
[electrical zapping]

21:22.406 --> 21:23.448
[grunting and bopping]

21:23.532 --> 21:24.908
[kids laughing]

21:24.992 --> 21:26.994
- ALL RIGHT,
THE APPEAL PROCESS IS OVER.

21:27.077 --> 21:29.329
NEXT TIME, DO A GOOD DEED.

21:29.413 --> 21:30.539
- WAIT, WAIT, WAIT.

21:30.622 --> 21:32.374
THEY DID DO A GOOD DEED.

21:32.457 --> 21:34.042
THEY BROUGHT SMILES
TO THE FACES

21:34.126 --> 21:36.211
OF THOSE POOR KIDS.

21:36.294 --> 21:37.379
[kids laughing]

21:37.462 --> 21:38.630
YOU KNOW WHAT?

21:38.714 --> 21:40.841
I'M SUPPOSED TO BE SHARING
MOZZARELLA STICKS

21:40.924 --> 21:42.551
WITH A TROLL FROM ACCOUNTING.

21:42.634 --> 21:44.970
YOU GUYS ARE OFFICIALLY
RUBBER STAMPED.

21:46.430 --> 21:47.597
- AWESOME!
- I RULE!

21:47.681 --> 21:48.890
- YES.
- OH.

21:48.974 --> 21:50.475
- COURSE, I WILL NEED YOU
TO SIGN

21:50.559 --> 21:52.269
A CONSENT-TO-REMAIN-WOOD FORM.

21:52.352 --> 21:53.645
[scribbling]

21:53.729 --> 21:55.063
- HUH?

21:55.147 --> 21:58.233
- I'M STILL A WOODEN BOY.

21:58.317 --> 22:00.360
COME ON, CHUM CHUM.

22:00.444 --> 22:01.319
- HEY, WHAT GIVES?

22:01.403 --> 22:03.697
SUDDENLY I'M A SLIMY AMPHIBIAN
OVER HERE.

22:03.780 --> 22:06.658
[croaks]

22:06.742 --> 22:07.784
- OOPS. HEH-HEH.

22:07.868 --> 22:11.455
I GUESS I GAVE YOU A
CONSENT-TO-REMAIN-A-FROG FORM.

22:11.538 --> 22:12.831
AH, WELL.

22:12.914 --> 22:15.083
THINGS ALWAYS GET A LITTLE MESSY
AROUND QUITTING TIME.

22:15.167 --> 22:16.710
poof!

22:16.793 --> 22:18.628
- NO, NO, YOU--

22:18.712 --> 22:20.505
YOU GOT TO TURN ME BACK
INTO MY BEAUTIFUL SELF.

22:20.589 --> 22:21.590
I LOVE ME.

22:21.673 --> 22:22.591
PLEASE DON'T GO AWAY.

22:22.674 --> 22:23.050
REVERSE IT.

22:23.133 --> 22:23.717
REVERSE IT.

22:23.800 --> 22:26.261
[croaks]

22:26.344 --> 22:28.138
LENNY, WAIT.

22:28.221 --> 22:29.931
YOU THINK YOU COULD GIVE ME
A KISS?

22:30.015 --> 22:31.099
- HA-HA-HA.

22:31.183 --> 22:32.309
RIGHT.

22:32.392 --> 22:32.976
- NO, I'M JUST TALKING
ABOUT A SMALL ONE,

22:33.060 --> 22:34.269
JUST A PECK, ALL RIGHT?

22:34.352 --> 22:36.480
YOU DON'T HAVE TO--
PLEASE, LENNY.

22:36.563 --> 22:37.606
YOU'RE MY ONLY HOPE.

22:40.984 --> 22:45.197
[melodic whistling]

22:45.280 --> 22:48.617
- WHOA!

22:48.700 --> 22:50.786
[quirky electronic music]

22:50.869 --> 22:54.748
♪ ♪

22:54.831 --> 22:57.626
[melodic whistling]

